textDelta: Moscow Treaty on Strategic Offensive Reductions The Moscow Treaty on Strategic Offensive Reductions, also referred to as the Strategic Offensive Reductions Treaty or SORT, is a bilateral treaty between the United States of America and the Russian Federation which was signed on 24 May 2002. It entered into force on 1 June 2003. The treaty was a follow-on to the Strategic Arms Reduction Treaty (START I), which had expired on December 5, 2009. It is expected to be superseded by the New START treaty.
